{"note":"<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901580\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909542\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909542\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; padding: 10px; margin: auto; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Managing Diversity in a Global Environment<\/span><\/strong><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">Welcome to <strong>Module 3.<\/strong>&nbsp;In this module, we will explore the importance of managing diversity in today's global business environment. You will learn about the benefits and challenges of diversity management, as well as the impact of globalization on organizations and managers.<\/p>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\">As you progress through the module, consider how you can effectively manage diverse employees and respond to the needs, attitudes, beliefs, and values they bring to the organization. Reflect on your own experiences with diversity and how they have shaped your perspective on management in a global context.<\/p>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><em>Need Support? Visit the <a title=\"Post your questions here\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78163\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78163\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Course Q&amp;A Discussion Board<\/a><\/em><\/p>\n    <hr \/>\n    <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><em>Time Commitment: Approximately 4 Hours<\/em><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901584\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909535\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909535\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Learning Objectives<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><strong>Through active engagement in this module, learners should be able to:<\/strong><\/p>\n    <ol class=\"list-decimal pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Articulate <\/strong>why effective management of diversity means more than hiring employees from diverse backgrounds. (CLO2)<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Describe<\/strong> the impact of the global environment on management. (CLO2)<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><strong>Connect <\/strong>empathy and vulnerability to a culture of love. (CLO3)<\/li>\n    <\/ol>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901585\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909544\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909544\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Learning Materials&nbsp;<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><em>The following carefully curated materials are designed to help you solidly understand this module's key concepts and principles.<\/em><\/p>\n    <h4><strong>Reading(s)<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <ul>\n        <li><strong>Contemporary Management<\/strong><\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <ul>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <ul class=\"list-disc pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 5: Managing Diverse Employees<\/li>\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 6: Managing in a Global Environment<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/li>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <div style=\"padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n                <details>\n                    <summary style=\"cursor: pointer;\"><em>Chapter Summaries<\/em><\/summary>\n                    <div style=\"padding: 5px 15px;\">\n                        <p><strong>Contemporary Management<\/strong><\/p>\n                        <ul>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 5 Managing Diverse Employees.<\/strong> The effective management of diversity means much more than hiring employees from diverse backgrounds. It also includes learning to appreciate and respond appropriately to the needs, attitudes, beliefs, and values that diverse people bring to an organization. Correcting misconceptions about why and how various employee groups differ and finding the most effective way to utilize the skills and talents of diverse employees are also part of the manager's responsibility. This chapter explores the increasing diversity in today's environment and how it can be proactively managed within the organization. It also explores why sometimes well-intentioned managers inadvertently treat one group of employees differently from another and the actions managers can take to ensure that diversity within the organization is respected.<\/li>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 6 Managing in a Global Environment.<\/strong> This chapter examines the organizations operating in a global environment. It identifies and examines the changing environmental forces that managers must learn to understand. These forces are divided into two categories: the task and the general. The chapter also discusses the impact on organizations and managers as companies compete for increased efficiency and effectiveness.<\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/details>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/li>\n        <li>\n            <p class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap break-words\"><strong>Love as a Business Strategy<\/strong><\/p>\n            <ul class=\"list-disc pl-8 space-y-2 -mt-1\">\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 5: Empathy<\/li>\n                <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\">Chapter 6: Vulnerability<\/li>\n            <\/ul>\n        <\/li>\n        <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n            <div style=\"padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px;\">\n                <details>\n                    <summary style=\"cursor: pointer;\"><em>Chapter Summaries<\/em><\/summary>\n                    <div style=\"padding: 5px 15px;\">\n                        <p><strong>Love as a Business Strategy<\/strong><\/p>\n                        <ul>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 5 Empathy.<\/strong> It's not easy to fully understand and embrace a situation that someone else is going through. Doing so requires not only a high level of emotional intelligence, but also a willingness to bear the same burden someone else might be experiencing. It is for these reasons that practicing empathy may be the most challenging Pillar of Love---and also the most critical. Empathy means understanding and sharing the emotional experience that someone else is having. It is a critical part of a culture of love.<\/li>\n                            <li><strong>Chapter 6 Vulnerability.<\/strong> Vulnerability, our third Pillar of Love, isn't always easy. It takes a lot of courage---one more time for the folks in the back---a lot of courage, but it's almost always worth it. In fact, we'd go so far as to say it's the secret sauce of building human relationships; when people see you being vulnerable, they want to be more vulnerable, too. Vulnerability is not about an open door, but rather an open person.<\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/details>\n            <\/div>\n        <\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <h4><strong>Multimedia<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <ul>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/chris_white_3_ways_to_create_a_work_culture_that_brings_out_the_best_in_employees\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">3 ways to Create a Work Culture that Brings out the Best in Employees<\/a> [12:39 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/christie_lindor_why_great_people_quit_good_jobs\/transcript?language=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Why People Quit Good Jobs<\/a> [14:35 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=0Mq2TiJmqCI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Putting the Human in Human Resources<\/a> [9:36 minutes]<\/li>\n        <li class=\"whitespace-normal break-words\"><a class=\"inline_disabled\" href=\"https:\/\/www.ted.com\/talks\/regina_hartley_why_the_best_hire_might_not_have_the_perfect_resume\/transcript?language=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Why the Best Hire May Not Have the Best Resume<\/a> [10:22 minutes]<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n<\/div>\n<div style=\"display: flex; text-align: center; margin-top: 10px;\">\n    <div class=\"\" style=\"background-color: #e45424; font-size: 14pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 5%;\"><img id=\"901586\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/files\/909539\/preview\" alt=\"\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/files\/909539\" data-api-returntype=\"File\" \/><\/div>\n    <h3 style=\"background-color: #eef4f9; font-size: 12pt; margin: auto; padding: 10px; width: 95%; text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Tasks to Complete or Submit<\/strong><\/span><\/h3>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"content-box\" style=\"margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; background-color: #f7f7f7; padding: 1.5% 2.5%;\">\n    <p><em>Completing the following tasks and assignments is crucial for demonstrating your understanding, applying your knowledge, and engaging with your peers and instructor.<\/em><\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸ“š<\/span><strong>Engage with Course Content<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Read the assigned chapters from Contemporary Management and Love as a Business Strategy to build a strong foundation in management and leadership principles. Watch the provided videos on leadership and management to gain insights from real-world examples and expert perspectives.<\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸ§©<\/span><strong>Assess Your Understanding<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Complete the <a title=\"Week #3 Quiz (CM Chapters 5-6, LAABS Chapters 5-6)\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140562\" data-course-type=\"quizzes.next\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140562\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Module 3 Quiz <\/a>to test your knowledge of the key concepts and principles covered in this module. The quiz is designed to reinforce your learning and provide feedback on areas for improvement. <strong>Due:<\/strong><\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸ’¬<\/span><strong>Participate in a Discussion or Attend a Zoom Session<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Contribute to the <a title=\"Module 3 Discussion Forum\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78160\" data-course-type=\"discussions\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/discussion_topics\/78160\" data-api-returntype=\"Discussion\">Module 3 Discussion<\/a> by sharing your thoughts, experiences, and questions about the course content. Engage with your classmates' posts to foster a collaborative learning environment. <strong>Due:<\/strong><span>&nbsp;<\/span>The initial post is due Thursday; the peer responses are due Sunday.<\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸš€<\/span><strong>Apply Your Knowledge<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Continue brainstorming ideas for the <a title=\"Course Spanning Project Part 1 - Leader Interview Presentation Draft\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140468\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140468\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Course Spanning Project Part 1<\/a>, which will allow you to apply the concepts and theories learned in this module to a real-world scenario. This project will be a key component of your learning journey and is due in Module 4. <span>You may also read ahead to learn about the expectations for the&nbsp;<\/span><a title=\"Course Spanning Project Part 2 - Leader Interview Presentation Final\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140476\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/140476\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Course Spanning Project Part 2.&nbsp;<\/a><\/p>\n    <p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n    <h4 class=\"whitespace-pre-wrap\"><span>ðŸŒŸ<\/span><strong>Continue Working on Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello<\/strong><\/h4>\n    <p>Remember to collaborate with your team on the ongoing <a title=\"Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello\" href=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/142488\" data-course-type=\"assignments\" data-published=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https:\/\/heidelberg.instructure.com\/api\/v1\/courses\/15770\/assignments\/142488\" data-api-returntype=\"Assignment\">Creating a Fictitious Company with Trello<\/a> assignment. Regularly communicate, assign tasks, and monitor progress to ensure a successful completion by the end of Module 6.<\/p>\n    <p>As you work on your teams, take a moment to reflect on your team's collaboration process:<\/p>\n    <ul>\n        <li>What worked well in your online collaboration? What challenges did you face, and how did you overcome them?<\/li>\n        <li>How did you apply the principles of management, motivation, leadership, and HR to create your fictitious company?<\/li>\n        <li>What insights did you gain from working with a diverse team, and how can you apply these lessons to future group projects or professional settings?<\/li>\n    <\/ul>\n    <p><em><strong>If you need support with team collaboration, reach out to your instructor.&nbsp;<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n    <hr \/>\n    <h4><span><strong>Engage with Your Instructor and Peers<\/strong><\/span><\/h4>\n    <p style=\"border-left: 4px solid #e45424; padding-left: 10px;\"><span><strong>Optional Zoom Session<\/strong>: During Modules 1, 3, and 6, you will have the option to join a LIVE Zoom discussion, which will replace this week's online discussion points if you attend. If you come prepared and participate fully in the Zoom discussion sessions, you will not be required to complete the Discussion Forum for this week, as this will replace it for you.<\/span><\/p>\n<\/div>\n<hr \/>\n<div style=\"background-color: #f2f4f8; color: #374a67; padding: 25px; width: 100%;\">\n    <h2 style=\"background-color: #e45424; color: #4e606a; padding: 25px; margin-bottom: 20px;\"><span style=\"color: #141414;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Summary<\/span> <span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">of This Module's Learning Tasks<\/span><\/strong><\/span><\/h2>\n    <div class=\"two-col-panels\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n        <div class=\"row\">\n            <div class=\"col-sm card bg-light\">\n                <ul>\n                    <li style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n                        <ul style=\"list-style-type: square;\">\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Monday<\/strong>: Engage with this Module's Content<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Wednesday<\/strong>: Complete Module 3 Quiz<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li>\n                                <p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Thursday<\/strong>: Initial Discussion Post Due<\/span><\/p>\n                            <\/li>\n                            <li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Sunday<\/strong>: Peer Response Due<\/span><\/li>\n                        <\/ul>\n                    <\/li>\n                <\/ul>\n           